context: The Obama administration began to reengage in Iraq with a series of airstrikes aimed at <b6_0>ISIS<b6_0/> beginning on <a0_0><b5_0>10 August 2014<b5_0/><a0_0/>. On 9 September 2014 President <b7_0>Obama<b7_0/> said that he had the authority he needed to take action to destroy the militant group known as the Islamic State of Iraq and the Levant, citing <a1_0>the 2001 <b8_0>Authorization for Use of Military Force Against Terrorists<b8_0/><a1_0/>, and thus did not require additional approval from Congress. The following day on <a2_0>10 September 2014<a2_0/> President Barack Obama made a televised speech about ISIL, which he stated "Our objective is clear: We will degrade, and ultimately destroy, ISIL through a comprehensive and sustained counter-terrorism strategy". Obama has authorized the deployment of additional U.S. Forces into Iraq, as well as authorizing direct military operations against ISIL within Syria. On the night of 21/22 September <a3_0>the <b9_0>United States, Saudi Arabia, Bahrain, the UAE, Jordan and Qatar<b9_0/><a3_0/> started air attacks against ISIS in <a4_0>Syria<a4_0/>.[citation needed]
